        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 6:02PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 601 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pinehurst, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tomball, Pinehurst, The Woodlands, Magnolia, Stagecoach, and Hooks
Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
